result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jesse Jermale Robinson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jesse Jermale Robinson was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Jesse Jermale Robinson was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Jesse Jermale Robinson was found guilty of Intentionally Mistreat Animals [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Surcharge], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 951.02.
  • Jesse Jermale Robinson was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Jesse Jermale Robinson was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

records.addlTxt: REQUEST TO ISSUE CIVIL JUDGMENT FOR RESTITUTION RECEIVED AND FORWARDED TO ALI. OS

Certification of transcript of proceedings of RETURN ON WARRANT commencing JUNE 06, 2016 received and filed. (6 Pages.)
Copy of transcript forwarded to PD

Defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson in custody.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  CASE HEARD FOR BRANCH 45.
Amended Information filed by the state.
Counts 1 ,2, 3 and 4 remain unchanged from Information filed on 1-11-2015.
Count 5:  Battery, a class A misdemeanor, 940.19(1)
Count 6:  Disorderly Conduct, Domestic Abuse, a class B misdemeanor, 947.01(1) and 973.055(1)
Pursuant to plea negotiations, AS TO COUNTS 2,3,4,5,6:   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgments of conviction entered.
COUNT 1 IS DISMISSED.
The state has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court from state, defense and defendant.
As to count 2:    The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, with credit for 35 days time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work and treatment.
As to count 3:    The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 2.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work and treatment.
As to count 4:    The court sentenced the defendant to serve 60 days in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 3 YEARS;
As to count 5:    The court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months  in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 4.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 3 YEARS, concurrent;
As to count 6:   The court sentenced the defendant to serve 90 days  in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 5.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 3 YEARS, concurrent;
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION as to counts 4,5,6:
-Attend and successfully complete Batterers Intervention OR Anger Management and continued programming.
-Mental health evaluation and take all prescribed medication(s), and/or treatment deemed appropriate.
-AODA and recommended treatment including random urine screens/Maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
-Parenting classes.
-Attend and successfully complete treatment and counseling programs as deemed appropriate by agent.
-NO CONTACT with the victim, UNLESS requested by victim and then only with prior approval of agent or the court.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-NO NEW LAW VIOLATIONS.
-Pay all MANDATORY costs, assessments, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by Dept of Corrections.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means. ANY CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO BE APPLIED.
-Provide DNA sample, pay costs and DNA surcharge.
-48 USC Section 922(g)(9) prohibits possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.
Defendant remanded.
RECEIVED & FILED: Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief; Pretrial Incarceration Credit; Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.
At request of counsels case set for plea/sentencing on 2-5-2016 at 8:15am.  Defendant to be produced from HOUSE OF CORRECTION.
Defense motion to modify bail is argued and denied.

Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.    Case set for final pretrial on 2-16-2016 at 8:15am.  Jury trial set for 2-29-2016 at 8:15am.  All final pretrial documents to be filed by the final pretrial hearing.  All motions to be filed by 2-1-2016.   Speedy trial demand.

Defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Det. Jeremy Harcus, St. Francis PD
State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss without argument.
Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.
  Final pre-trial scheduled for February 16, 2016 at 08:15 am.  Jury trial scheduled for February 29, 2016 at 08:15 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.  The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.    Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Dennaeyia B and all of her family or Mount Mary University.

Defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson in court with attorney Paige Aleece Styler.  Defendant Jesse Jermale Robinson in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Wagner, Branch 38.  Defense moves to dismiss Count 5 for lack of probable cause.  Arguments heard.  Court GRANTS motion to dismiss Count 5.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  Defense entered a plea of NOT GUILTY as to Counts 2, 3 & 4.  DEFENDANT DOES NOT QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION IF RELEASED FROM CUSTODY.  
  Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he/she may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he/she meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).

  Preliminary hearing scheduled for January 11, 2016 at 08:15 am.
